---
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: 'Stefan Taitano'
description: 'Army veteran turned ServiceNow consultant, documenting the path to CTA certification, backend development, and relocating a family of four on a big adventure.'
articles:
  title: 'Recent Articles'
  intro: 'A few things I have written lately.'
---

<div class="wrapper">
  <header class="full | section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-primary)">
    <div class="section__inner flow region" style="--region-space-top: var(--space-xl-2xl); --region-space-bottom: var(--space-xl-2xl);">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div
          style="display: flex; gap: var(--space-xl); align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap;"
        >
          <div class="flow" style="flex: 1; min-inline-size: 28ch; max-inline-size: 62ch;">
            <h1 style="color: var(--color-light);">I build systems for a living and escape plans for fun.</h1>
            <p style="font-size: var(--size-step-1); color: var(--color-light); opacity: 0.95;">
              I'm Stefan, an Army veteran turned ServiceNow consultant, currently deep in CTA certification prep
              and teaching myself backend development.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--color-light); opacity: 0.95;">
              This site is where I write about tech, life design, and the patterns that show up when you pay
              attention across domains.
            </p>
            <div class="cluster gutter-s" style="margin-top: var(--space-m);">
              <a href="/now/" class="button" data-button-variant="tertiary">See what I'm doing now</a>
              <a href="/articles/" class="button" data-ghost-button>Read the articles</a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <figure
            aria-label="Stefan Taitano"
            style="flex-shrink: 0; inline-size: min(260px, 100%); aspect-ratio: 1; border-radius: 50%; overflow: hidden; border: 4px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-light) 35%, transparent);"
          >
            <img
              src="/assets/images/stefan.png"
              alt="Stefan Taitano"
              width="260"
              height="260"
              style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center 20%;"
            >
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% svg "divider/waves", null, "divider" %}
  </header>

  <section id="now-preview" class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div
        class="flow"
        style="background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-bg-accent-2); border-radius: var(--border-radius-medium); padding: var(--space-l);"
      >
        <p style="font-size: var(--size-step-min-1); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">
          What I'm doing now
        </p>
        <div class="flow">
          <p>Preparing for ServiceNow's Certified Technical Architect exam.</p>
          <p>Learning Python and Go through Boot.dev's backend path.</p>
          <p>Playing chess on <a href="https://lichess.org/@/Late2TheBoard">Lichess</a> and improving slowly.</p>
          <p>Writing on <a href="https://medium.com/@stefantaitano">Medium</a> about what I'm figuring out.</p>
        </div>
        <p><a href="/now/">See the full /now page</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
      <div class="flow">
        <p style="font-size: var(--size-step-min-1); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em;">
          Explore the site
        </p>
        <h2>Pick a trail.</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid" style="--grid-placement: auto-fit; --grid-min-item-size: 16rem;">
        <a
          href="/articles/"
          style="display: block; padding: var(--space-l); border: 1px solid var(--color-bg-accent-2); border-radius: var(--border-radius-medium); text-decoration: none;"
        >
          <strong>Articles</strong>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--space-xs);">Tech, life design, and cross-domain thinking.</p>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/#projects"
          style="display: block; padding: var(--space-l); border: 1px solid var(--color-bg-accent-2); border-radius: var(--border-radius-medium); text-decoration: none;"
        >
          <strong>Projects</strong>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--space-xs);">Things I'm building and have built.</p>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/#newsletter"
          style="display: block; padding: var(--space-l); border: 1px solid var(--color-bg-accent-2); border-radius: var(--border-radius-medium); text-decoration: none;"
        >
          <strong>Field Notes</strong>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--space-xs);">My occasional newsletter on building, moving, and figuring it out.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="prose wrapper flow">
      <h2>{{ articles.title }}</h2>
      {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
      {% if itemList.length > 0 %}
        {% if articles.intro %}
          <p>{{ articles.intro }}</p>
        {% endif %}
      {% else %}
        <p>
          The archive is just getting started. For now, you can browse <a href="/articles/">the articles page</a>
          or read newer writing on <a href="https://medium.com/@stefantaitano">Medium</a>.
        </p>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="feature | region region-space-l">
        {% if itemList.length > 0 %}
          <custom-masonry layout="50-50">
            {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 3) %}
              {% set headingLevel = "h3" %}
              {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
            {% endeach %}
          </custom-masonry>
        {% endif %}
      </div>
      <p><a href="/articles/">Browse all articles</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="projects" class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <div
        class="flow"
        style="background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-bg-accent-2); border-radius: var(--border-radius-medium); padding: var(--space-l);"
      >
        <h2>Projects</h2>
        <p>
          This section will grow into a proper projects page, but it already points at the themes behind the work:
          backend learning, AI tools, de-Googling, relocation systems, and the experiments that come with building in
          public.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="prose wrapper flow">
      <h2>A bit more about me</h2>
      <p>
        Before tech, I served in the United States Army as a Fire Control Specialist, working as a Team Lead,
        Program Manager, and Retention Manager. The military taught me how to build teams, run processes, and operate
        in ambiguity, skills that turned out to transfer directly into consulting.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days I work as a ServiceNow Technical Consultant, helping organizations automate and streamline their
        workflows. I'm pursuing the CTA certification because I want to architect solutions, not just be a code monkey.
        On a parallel track, I'm learning backend development through Boot.dev, Python and Go, with no rush and no
        pressure.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I read constantly, train when I can, and think a lot about intentional life design -
        building a life that fits rather than one that just happened.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="newsletter" class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper">
      {% include "partials/newsletter-cta.njk" %}
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
